es up to 10$^{11}M_{\\odot} -$\nsignificantly above the mass scales predicted to have increased scatter from\ncurrent hydrodynamical models. The sparse satellite population of this `lonely\ngiant' thus advocates for an important modification to ideas of how the\nsatellites around MW-mass galaxies form.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jul 2018 17:59:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 Aug 2018 15:53:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-21"}
