ing in the surroundings of\nR136. Massive stars within a projected distance of 8 pc of R136 are not coeval\nbut show an age range of up to 6 Myr. Our mass distributions are well populated\nup to $200\\,\\mathrm{M}_\\odot$. The inferred IMF is shallower than a\nSalpeter-like IMF and appears to be the same across 30 Dor. By comparing our\nsample of stars to stellar models in the Hertzsprung-Russell diagram, we find\nevidence for missing physics in the models above $\\log L/\\mathrm{L}_\\odot=6$\nthat is likely connected to enhanced wind mass loss for stars approaching the\nEddington limit. [abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Jul 2018 18:41:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
